Luckily, I'm only running a nginx webserver hosting a few html pages, for the sole purpose of Coinhive attacks. And who the fuck uses php anymore? I have no reason to be running phpMyAdmin. Now I have even fewer reasons to do so...

The CloudFail scans on my own webserver also do not reveal my IP address.. which means that these vulnerability scans would have likely bounced off of CloudFlare. CloudFail will only ever reveal your IP, if you've misconfigured your DNS settings... or if for some reason you show up on CrimeFlare.org (in which case, you're either ISIS, or some kiddy porn site.)

